{
  "text": "Remark. For a finite group G, there is a one-to-one correspondence between the set of fusions of the association scheme induced by G by its regular action and the set of Schur rings over G (see [CITATION_1] for the definition of Schur ring). Thus Problem 1.2 can be stated in terms of Schur rings.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "7751007"
  },
  "bib_entries": {
    "7751007": {
      "title": "Schur rings",
      "abstract": "In this paper we survey the recent developments in the theory of Schur rings and its applications to different problems that appear in theory of association schemes, Cayley graphs and other parts of algebraic combinatorics."
    }
  }
}